A: You can use a TreeMap to store the name and score.
TreeMap<String, Integer> map = new TreeMap<String, Integer>();

Then you can add the name and score to the map.
map.put(name, score);

Then you can sort the map by the score.
Map<String, Integer> sortedMap = new TreeMap<String, Integer>(new Comparator<String>() {
    public int compare(String o1, String o2) {
        return map.get(o2).compareTo(map.get(o1));
    }
});
sortedMap.putAll(map);

Then you can print the sorted map.
for (Map.Entry<String, Integer> entry : sortedMap.entrySet()) {
    System.out.println(entry.getKey() + " " + entry.getValue());
}
